value.0: "Your companions live again, though it was a struggle to bring them back after such a long time in my goddess's domain."
"I see you have returned. What can I do for you?"
"I am Lavos, servant of Mistress Death." The woman's lips barely seem to move as she speaks and her face is startlingly pale. She chuckles at your surprise.
"Death greets you, <FirstName>, waiting with eternal patience. You are welcome in this place, though why, I do not understand."

Comment.value: set that pc knows about Lavos's vision

value.0: "I have a had vision, a glorious vision of Mistress Death, and she told me to assist you. She sent a spirit to me, and I gave the spirit the ability to bring you back from my Mistress's realm."
"Such wonders are rare to behold and such requests rarer still. I can feel the presence of the spirit in your weapon. So do you know why my goddess favors you?"
"Whether you worship her or not is of no matter. Death must follow you, wherever you go. I guess we shall discover the reason in time. So how may I be of service?"
"That is the mark of one favored, but it does not explain why you are favored. I guess we shall discover the reason in time. So how may I be of service?"
"That is a possibility, though there are many who enjoy killing, and few of them have ever held such favor, even within the church. How may I be of service to you?"
"That is unfortunate. I guess we shall discover the reason in time. So how may I be of service?"
"We shall see each other again; whether in this world or the next, who can say?"
"The mysteries of death require great study. It might be that I can answer a question or two for you."
"And what might your other concerns be?"
"What interest have I in politics or worldly affairs? My time is better spent in researching the mysteries of death and guarding over my sacred duties as a servant of the Mistress."
"If my Mistress ever decided I should have more influence, then I would do what I had to. I doubt I shall be called to such a task though. People take more comfort from a leader like Dynschall."
"Shrouded in her darkest gown, with a lustrous hood of royal color, she came to me and spoke of a <man/woman> of great importance who would serve her well."
"She even showed me your face and asked that I give some of my life force to the spirit she would send."
"I gave up that part of my life force and I still feel quite weak, but I can feel my powers returning, so the Goddess is still with me."
"The mysteries of death take years to glean, and even after a lifetime of service dedicated to my Mistress, I find there is more to learn than when I started."
"Mistress Death has always been and will always be, for where there is life, there must also be death."
"Ah, so the Lady Rehan has been tormenting you with her sorrow, has she?"
"If a spirit is not at rest, there is often a reason for it, <FirstName>. As a priestess of Mistress Death, exorcism is a task I cannot take lightly. But, if it is important to you, I shall do it."
"She was a noblewoman here in Cyan, young and beautiful. She had a melancholy about her, though, a wistfulness that made her seem a ghost even while still alive."

"One morning, she threw herself from a cliff. When the soldiers carried her broken body to me, I remember them commenting that she had the look about her of one in love... She has haunted that Manor ever since."
"Important enough that you would sacrifice one charge of that magic weapon you carry with you? Its powers are strong but even they will not last forever."
"Perhaps you'd better not indeed, <FirstName>. If you are going to request an exorcism, you had best have the stomach for it..."
"I thought that might be the case, <FirstName>... It's interesting what we living hold dear, is it not?"

Lavos lays her hand upon your weapon, her eyes rolling back to show their whites. The air around her seems to grow thick. "Thank you, <FirstName>. By the time you return to home, the deed will be done."
"That is true, if my Mistress grants me such high power. I am one of the few in these lands who do. Your weapon also has that power though."
"Is there aught else I can do for you?"
"Do you think that such powers are just handed out to any priest? If life were so cheaply bought, we would have no fear, no justifiable reasons to develop society."
"The mysteries of death's great power are not easily purchased. My life is partially consumed to bring back a lost soul."

"This is a price I gladly pay, for in death, my Mistress shall lift me up beside her in the halls of the dead. But so long as she wants me to live, I will serve her here and protect my power and my life.""
"The power to bring a soul back is not to be taken lightly. It is a complex and draining power. Be careful what you ask for."
"However, since I was told to assist you in any way I could, if you bring me their bodies, I shall do this for you."
"The task would be harder on me than on you. That said, it is your decision to make, not mine. Is there aught else I can do for you?"
"Very well. Is their anything else you would like?"

value.0: "I have already said that I would vote for you. Do not make me lose patience and change my mind!"
"For Death to do such a thing is unnatural. I don't like where this is leading us, <FirstName>."
"That be the voice, <FirstName>. The new one in my head. Why would Death be interested in you being alive though?"
"That is a strange thing for Mistress Death to do, <FirstName>. I fear what consequences might wait in the path before us."
"Death greets me?"
"What do you mean?"
"I find even the idea repugnant."
"Death seems to follow in my wake."
"Maybe because I enjoy killing."
"I have no idea."
"Goodbye."
"I have other questions for you."
"I have other concerns."
"You seem powerful. Why aren't you the guildmaster?"
"Tell me more about your vision."
"Tell me about your goddess."
"I own a house that is in need of an exorcism."
"Her sorrows? What do you mean?"
"Lady Rehan?"
"Yes, and I want it stopped at once."
"Tell me about this Lady Rehan."
"Perhaps I'd better not have the house exorcised after all."
"Well it's important that the house be exorcised."
"It's very important. My house must be exorcised at once."
"Perhaps I'd better not..."
"I don't think my weapon has any charges to spare."
"Yes, I will sacrifice one charge of my weapon."
"You said you have the power to raise the dead."
"I guess you're right."
"Why one of the few?"
"I would like to raise my other companions."
"That's just too much work."
